      "comment": "OZZIE PEARL (6) was a beaten favourite here last week but the effort still had merit when she led and boxed on for third last, beaten 5.3 metres. Draws wider but she is suited against her own sex and is up to winning this if things go her way. CORAL CAYS (8) came from this row and missed by a nose when second here last week. Owns a decent record over this longer distance including a win from a similar draw here three back. Big chance if things go her way. TABRA (5) should be close to peak fitness and is looming as a threat after a better effort last start, coming from the back row and finishing second at this venue. HEAVENLY TURBO (4) is first-up for four-and-a-half months but was racing well last time in and was readied with a solid trial.",
